                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="anderson_sng_4" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1876-1941) a US writer. His most successful collection of short stories was <span class="ebi">Winesburg, Ohio</span> (1919) about the boring life of a small town. His novels included <span class="ebi">Poor White</span> (1920) and <span class="ebi">Dark Laughter</span> (1925).</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
